oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real Picture post card of French Renault FT Tank
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Real picture post card of a French tank. It was one of the first tanks adopted to have a turret and was used by the French initially but also by American tankers. The image belonged to William R. Smith of Rutherford County, Tennessee. Smith served as a motor mechanic in the signal corps. He served in France from July 15, 1918 to May 30, 1919. He was discharged June 17, 1919.
